<subSubSection id="FC8E653B875AB10018715093FBF1F806" pageId="21" pageNumber="214" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875AB10018715093FA81F93D" blockId="21.[808,1400,1665,2083]" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875AB10018715093FC57F967" bold="true" box="[808,963,1665,1690]" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB10018865093FCF9F93D" authority="Merriam" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1889" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="214" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fallax">Perognathus fallax Merriam, 1889</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED875AB1001827508DFA81F93D" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894358" box="[894,1301,1695,1728]" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">“San Bernardino, Cal.,” USA.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875AB100187050D5FBF1F806" blockId="21.[808,1400,1665,2083]" pageId="21" pageNumber="214">
Based on detailed sequencing of nDNA and mtDNA genes, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB1001F1B50FCFB3BF8F2" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1889" box="[1090,1199,1774,1807]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="215" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fallax">C. fallax</taxonomicName>
is a close relative of 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB10018C15104FBC1F8CA" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[920,1109,1814,1847]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="215" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="californicus">C. californicus</taxonomicName>
, and both are part of the Baja California Peninsula lineage of the “modern” clade of coarse-haired pocket mice, along with C. ammophilus, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB100187251AEFC5FF828" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1894" box="[811,971,1980,2005]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenarius">C. arenarius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB10018B851AEFBC4F828" baseAuthorityName="Osgood" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[993,1104,1980,2005]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="213" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="siccus">C. siccus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875AB1001FFE51AEFAAEF828" baseAuthorityName="Merriam" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1191,1338,1980,2005]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="21" pageNumber="216" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spinatus">C. spinatus</taxonomicName>
. Six subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
